<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 5:21PM CDT  by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF EASTERN BURKE COUNTY
THROUGH 600 PM CDT...
At 520 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Lignite, or 32
miles east of Crosby, moving southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts to 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lignite and Flaxton around 525 PM CDT.
Bowbells around 535 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
